snippet.textDisplay:
I am the ever-so-drunk Sufi, 
 No one has a clue of my way.
 میں صوفی ہوں سرمستا، میرا کون پہچانے رستا 

(These Sufis) carry the breath upwards from Nabh Kanwal (1)
 They illuminate Hirday Kanwal(2) (near heart, centre of chest) 
 (finally) In the Bhanwar Gupha (3) they get visualization
 After which fall the rain of love from the clouds.

 نابھ کنول سوں دم الٹاون، ھردے کنول میں جوت جگاون
 بھنور غفا میں درشن پاون، بادل برہ برستا 

My Spiritual Guide drank me rich drink
 The bond of living and dying at once broke
 I felt such intoxication of love
 that  my Spiritual Guide and I became one and smiled in joy 

ستگر جام پلايا گهوٹا، جنم مرن کا بندھن ٹوٹا
 عشق پریم کا آیا جھوٹا، ھر رام میرے سنگ ہنستا 

I wore Hindu-thread and applied mark on forehead (adopted ways of negating my self)
 I played flute of Ohang Suhang (I took breath upwards and downwards from Nabh Kanwal to Bhanwar Gupha)
 I became heathen and brought my Beloved round
 This way I became and Birhman (idolator) of one heavenly figure

 جنیا پاکے تلگ لگایم، اوونگ سوونگ بین بجایم
 مشرک تھی محبوب منایم، برہمن بت پرستا

 I received such a blow from heaven 
 that day and night I roamed as a strayed-one
 Finally I found the same Beloved
 that Mohan (Beloved) resided in my heart

 چوٹ گگن میں ایسی لاگی، نس دن بن میں پھروں بیراگی

 ڈھونڈ لدھم گھر سانول ساگی، موھن من میں بستا 

Ali Mohammad say this upside-down language
 What do people know about it?
 This riddle is understood by a sadhu/sant (well-versed Sufi)
 I have prepared a bouquet from the verses

 علی محمد ای اُلٹی بولی، کیا جانے خلقت بھولی
 کو سمجھے سادھو سنت پرولی، شعر بَنا گُلدستا
 __________________ 


Poetry: Hazrat Sufi Faqeer Ali Mohammad Talpur

 _________
 footnotes:
 1. Nabh Kanwal: (Nabh Kaml /Manipurna) (spiritual energy point) is 
located within your spinal column. It can be found parallel to your 
navel. 
 2. Hriday Kanwal: (Hridaya Kaml, Surya) It is located in the
 region of the heart, in the centre of the chest. Hriday means heart

 3. Bhanwar Gupha: (literally, whirling or rotating cave) It is also 
called Sohang region. It is located is behind the Eyes. It is higher 
plane than tirkuti (between two eyes)

 علی محمد ای اُلٹی بولی، کیا جانے خلقت بھولی
 کو سمجھے سادھو سنت پرولی، شعر بَنا گُلدستا
 __________________ 


Poetry: Hazrat Sufi Faqeer Ali Mohammad Talpur

 _________
 footnotes:
 1. Nabh Kanwal: (Nabh Kaml /Manipurna) (spiritual energy point) is 
located within your spinal column. It can be found parallel to your 
navel. 
 2. Hriday Kanwal: (Hridaya Kaml, Surya) It is located in the
 region of the heart, in the centre of the chest. Hriday means heart

 3. Bhanwar Gupha: (literally, whirling or rotating cave) It is also 
called Sohang region. It is located is behind the Eyes. It is higher 
plane than tirkuti (between two eyes)
